PROGRAM: TaskMaster CLI
TECH: C++ (Standard), STL

// >>> DATA STRUCTURES:
// 1. Define a struct 'Task' with:
//    - int id
//    - string description
//    - bool completed
// 2. Use a global 'std::vector<Task>' to store the tasks.
// 3. Keep track of a 'nextId' counter to assign unique IDs.

// >>> PERSISTENCE (File I/O):
// - Create a function 'loadTasks()':
//   - Open 'tasks.db' (text file).
//   - Read line by line. Format expected: "id|completed|description".
//   - Parse lines and fill the vector.
// - Create a function 'saveTasks()':
//   - Open 'tasks.db' for writing (overwrite).
//   - Loop through vector and write: "id|completed|description" for each task.

// >>> MAIN LOGIC:
// 1. Load tasks on startup.
// 2. Loop forever showing prompt "taskmaster > ".
// 3. COMMANDS:
//    - "add [text]": Create a new task. Example: "add Buy Milk". (Use getline to get full text).
//    - "list": Show all tasks. Format: "[X] 1. Buy Milk" (if done) or "[ ] 1. Buy Milk" (if not).
//    - "done [id]": Find task by ID and set completed = true.
//    - "del [id]": Find task by ID and remove it from vector.
//    - "help": Show commands.
//    - "exit": Call saveTasks() and terminate program.

